{
  "doc_id": "1722",
  "text": "Cyclooxygenase (COX)-2 serves an important role in the tumorigenesis of various types of cancer, and COX-2 inhibitors may effectively prevent tumor progression [CITATION_1] . Celecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor; at the early stages of non-small-cell lung cancer (NSCLC), celecoxib was reported to increase the anti-cancer properties of preoperative chemotherapies, such as paclitaxel and carboplatin [CITATION_2] . In addition, celecoxib treatment upregulated the expression of death receptor 5 (DR5), decreased cell survival and induced apoptosis in NSCLCs [CITATION_3] .",
